article.headline: Florida Atlantic 94, Florida Memorial 60
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Carlos Monroe got 28 points and 13 rebounds to lead Florida Atlantic to a 94-60 victory over Florida Memorial Tuesday. Monroe shot 13-of-16 from the floor. Derrick Simmons got 17 points and Sean Alarcon got 12. The Lions (2-4) started the game on a 7-2 run over the first 1:55, but the Owls came back with a 7-2 run. The Owls (2-4) had a 44-35 lead at halftime. Monroe scored a team-high 11 points in the first half and grabbed seven rebounds. Simmons added nine first-half points on a 3-for-3 effort and a 3-for-4 first half from the free throw line. Graham contributed eight points and four assists. David Anderson set a career-high with three blocks in the first half. Tramaine Stevens got 19 points for the Lions on 8-of-18 shooting, while Andre Beauford got 16 points.
